<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="py-12 bg-white sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
  <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-7xl sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl xl:text-5xl font-pj">
        Frequently Asked Questions
      </h2>
      <p class="max-w-lg mx-auto mt-6 text-base text-gray-600 font-pj">
        Navigate our FAQs and unearth the wordy treasures hidden within!
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-8 sm:mt-14">
      <div x-data="{ active: 1 }" class="space-y-4">
        <div class="relative">
          <div class="absolute -inset-1">
            <div
              class="w-full h-full mx-auto opacity-30 blur-lg filter"
              style="background: linear-gradient(90deg, #44ff9a -0.55%, #44b0ff 22.86%, #8b44ff 48.36%, #ff6644 73.33%, #ebff70 99.34%)"
            >
            </div>
          </div>

          <div
            x-data="{
                          id: 1,
                          get expanded() {
                              return this.active === this.id
                          },
                          set expanded(value) {
                              this.active = value ? this.id : null
                          },
                      }"
            role="region"
            class="relative overflow-hidden bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl"
          >
            <h3>
              <button
                @click="expanded = !expanded"
                x-bind:aria-expanded="expanded"
                class="flex items-center justify-between w-full px-6 py-5 text-xl font-bold text-left text-gray-900 sm:p-8 font-pj"
              >
                <span> How does it compare to traditional localization tools? </span>
                <span x-show="expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                  <svg
                    class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M20 12H4"
                    />
                  </svg>
                </span>
                <span x-show="!expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                  <svg
                    class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                    xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                    fill="none"
                    viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                    stroke="currentColor"
                  >
                    <path
                      stroke-linecap="round"
                      stroke-linejoin="round"
                      stroke-width="2"
                      d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"
                    />
                  </svg>
                </span>
              </button>
            </h3>

            <div x-show="expanded" x-collapse>
              <div class="px-6 pb-6 sm:px-8 sm:pb-8">
                Glossia redefines localization by dismissing traditional, linear solutions that often force users to choose between speed and quality. Unlike conventional tools, we draw inspiration from compiler approaches to programming languages, <b>modeling content and context as an interconnected graph</b>. Utilizing
                <a
                  class="underline"
                  target="_blank"
                  href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Large_language_model"
                >
                  Large Language Models (LLMs)
                </a>
                enables us to balance quality and speed through an intricate understanding of semantic relationships. We believe the industry, plagued by an acute <a
                  class="underline"
                  href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunk_cost"
                  target="_blank"
                >sunk cost fallacy</a>, demands a foundational reevaluation and innovative rethinking of established models.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          x-data="{
                          id: 2,
                          get expanded() {
                              return this.active === this.id
                          },
                          set expanded(value) {
                              this.active = value ? this.id : null
                          },
                      }"
          role="region"
          class="overflow-hidden bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl"
        >
          <h3>
            <button
              @click="expanded = !expanded"
              x-bind:aria-expanded="expanded"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full px-6 py-5 text-xl font-bold text-left text-gray-900 sm:p-8 font-pj"
            >
              <span>Can't I just use Google Translate or DeepL? </span>
              <span x-show="expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M20 12H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span x-show="!expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </h3>

          <div x-show="expanded" x-collapse>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 sm:px-8 sm:pb-8">
              <p>
                Many organizations, including those utilizing localization tools with machine translation, often resort to solutions like
                <a href="https://translate.google.com/" target="_blank" class="underline">
                  Google Translate
                </a>
                or <a href="https://www.deepl.com" target="_blank" class="underline">DeepL</a>, despite their lack of context-awareness resulting in suboptimal translations. Unlike them, Large Language Models (LLMs), which are employed for localization, capably utilize context. Our primary challenge—and focus—is to <b>harness and deliver the right context</b>, ensuring models not only improve over time but also excel in their localization tasks. This pivotal role is where Glossia steps in.
              </p>
              <p>
                By significantly reducing localization costs without sacrificing quality, Glossia <b>unlocks an expansive world of localization possibilities</b>. Now, targeting is not confined to languages but extends to specific countries, communities, or even age demographics, offering boundless opportunities.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          x-data="{
                                        id: 3,
                                        get expanded() {
                                            return this.active === this.id
                                        },
                                        set expanded(value) {
                                            this.active = value ? this.id : null
                                        },
                                    }"
          role="region"
          class="overflow-hidden bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl"
        >
          <h3>
            <button
              @click="expanded = !expanded"
              x-bind:aria-expanded="expanded"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full px-6 py-5 text-xl font-bold text-left text-gray-900 sm:p-8 font-pj"
            >
              <span> Will you provide an Developer API? </span>
              <span x-show="expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M20 12H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span x-show="!expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </h3>

          <div x-show="expanded" x-collapse>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 sm:px-8 sm:pb-8">
              Including a developer API is a key component of our plan. After orchestrating content sources and establishing models to effectively capture and utilize context, we aim for Glossia to <b>become the backend for platforms hosting content</b>, elevating languages to a first-class citizen status. Our experience at <a
                href="https://shopify.com"
                target="_blank"
                class="underline"
              >Shopify</a>, a global commerce platform, highlighted a striking realization: <i>languages were seldom prioritized as a core component of the platform</i>. Often, organizations couldn’t shoulder the costs of integrating languages into their platform’s fundamental architecture, relegating this responsibility to their developer ecosystem. Glossia intends to shift this paradigm. To do so, we're committed to providing organizations with a developer API, allowing them to integrate with Glossia’s foundational models and logic, thereby transforming language localization and incorporation.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          x-data="{
                                          id: 4,
                                          get expanded() {
                                              return this.active === this.id
                                          },
                                          set expanded(value) {
                                              this.active = value ? this.id : null
                                          },
                                      }"
          role="region"
          class="overflow-hidden bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl"
        >
          <h3>
            <button
              @click="expanded = !expanded"
              x-bind:aria-expanded="expanded"
              class="flex items-center justify-between w-full px-6 py-5 text-xl font-bold text-left text-gray-900 sm:p-8 font-pj"
            >
              <span> How do you ensure localization quality? </span>
              <span x-show="expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M20 12H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
              <span x-show="!expanded" aria-hidden="true" class="ml-4">
                <svg
                  class="w-6 h-6 text-gray-900"
                  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                  fill="none"
                  viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                  stroke="currentColor"
                >
                  <path
                    stroke-linecap="round"
                    stroke-linejoin="round"
                    stroke-width="2"
                    d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"
                  />
                </svg>
              </span>
            </button>
          </h3>

          <div x-show="expanded" x-collapse>
            <div class="px-6 pb-6 sm:px-8 sm:pb-8">
              Quality is at the heart of Glossia. Our AI-powered system learns and improves over time, but we also rely on the invaluable human touch and feedback. Glossia believes in a synergy between AI and human translators, ensuring top-notch translation quality while reducing costs and increasing speed.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<!-- Team -->
<section class="py-12 bg-white sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
  <div class="px-4 mx-auto max-w-7xl sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">Meet Our Dedicated Team</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 px-8 mt-12 text-center sm:px-0 sm:gap-6 sm:mt-16 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="overflow-hidden bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-md">
